  "prompt": "How many known viruses can infect humans?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2021, it was estimated that there are over 200 known viruses that can infect humans. This includes well-known viruses such as influenza, HIV, hepatitis viruses, and coronaviruses, as well as many others that cause a range of illnesses from mild colds to severe diseases. \n\nHowever, as new viruses are discovered and the understanding of existing viruses evolves, this number can change. Additionally, the emergence of new viruses through zoonotic spillover (viruses jumping from animals to humans) can also increase the total count. For the most accurate and current information, I recommend consulting reliable public health sources or scientific literature.",
